The paper discusses the use of evolutionary computation (EC) to solve the graph partitioning problem (GPP), which is a combinatorial optimization problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
